While fiddling around with color prompts, I noticed this quirk:

PS1="%B${PURPLE}%m${NORMAL}%(#.#.>)%b "

does not display the > (or #) in bold, while

PS1="%B${PURPLE}%m${NORMAL}%b%B%(#.#.>)%b "

does.

